ue]], American race car driver and engineer (b. 1937) *[[1976]] &ndash; [[Alastair Sim]], Scottish-English actor (b. 1900) * 1976 &ndash; [[Ken Wadsworth]], New Zealand cricketer (b. 1946) *[[1977]] &ndash; [[Aleksander Kreek]], Estonian shot putter and discus thrower (b. 1914) * 1977 &ndash; [[Groucho Marx]], American comedian and actor (b. 1890) *[[1980]] &ndash; [[Otto Frank]], German-Swiss businessman, father of [[Anne Frank]] (b. 1889) *[[1981]] &ndash; [[Jessie Matthews]], English actress, singer, and dancer (b. 1907) *[[1982]] &ndash; [[August Neo]], Estonian wrestler (b. 1908) *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Hermione Baddeley]], English actress (b. 1906) *[[1993]] &ndash; [[Utpal Dutt]], Bangladeshi actor, director, and playwright (b. 1929) *[[1994]] &ndash; [[Linus Pauling]], American chemist and biologist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1901) *[[1995]] &ndash; [[Pierre Schaeffer]], French composer and musicologist (b. 1910) *[[2000]] &ndash; [[Bineshwar Brahma]], Indian poet, author, and educator (b. 1948) * 2000 &ndash; [[Theodore Trautwein]], American lawyer and judge (b. 1920) *[[2001]] &ndash; [[Donald Woods]], South African journalist and activist (b. 1933) *[[2003]] &ndash; [[Carlos Roberto Reina]], Honduran lawyer and politician, [[President of Honduras]] (b. 1926) * 2003 &ndash; [[Sérgio Vieira de Mello]], Brazilian diplomat (b. 1948) *[[2005]] &ndash; [[Mo Mowlam]], English academic and politician, [[Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster]] (b. 1949) *[[2008]] &ndash; [[Levy Mwanawasa]], Zambian lawyer and politician, 3rd [[President of Zambia]] (b. 1948) *[[2009]] &ndash; [[Don Hewitt]], American television producer, created ''[[60 Minutes]]'' (b. 1922) *[[2011]] &ndash; [[Raúl Ruiz (director)|Raúl Ruiz]], Chilean director and producer (b. 1941) *[[2012]] &ndash; [[Donal Henahan]], American journalist and critic (b. 1921) * 2012 &ndash; [[Ivar Iversen]], Norwegian canoe racer (b. 1914) * 2012 &ndash; [[Tony Scott]], English-American dire